                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-18T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >May 18, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 18—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>400. 1. Following from American Consul at Swatow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“May 17, 4 p.m. Kwangsi adherents evacuating Swatow hurriedly. … Due to
                            the possibility of disorders during the period of transition…, I request
                            the presence of an American warship, if one be available.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. Message has been repeated to commander in chief United States Asiatic Fleet
                    with my concurrence in request.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
